1858 // First off we need to decide how tall the skirt must be.
1859 // The skirt_height option from config is expressed in layers, but our
1860 // object might have different layer heights, so we need to find the print_z

1862 // Note that unless has_infinite_skirt() == true
1863 // the actual skirt might not reach this $skirt_height_z value since the print

1165 m_model.objects.reserve(model.objects.size());
1166 auto by_id_lower = [](const ModelObject *lhs, const ModelObject *rhs){ return lhs->id() < rhs->id(); };
1167 std::sort(model_objects_old.begin(), model_objects_old.end(), by_id_lower);
1168 for (const ModelObject *mobj : model.objects) {
1169 auto it = std::lower_bound(model_objects_old.begin(), model_objects_old.end(), mobj, by_id_lower);
1170 if (it == model_objects_old.end() || (*it)->id() != mobj->id()) {
1171 // New ModelObject added.
1172 m_model.objects.emplace_back(ModelObject::new_copy(*mobj));
1173 m_model.objects.back()->set_model(&m_model);
1174 model_object_status_db.add(*mobj, ModelObjectStatus::New);
1175 } else {
1176 // Existing ModelObject re-added (possibly moved in the list).
1177 m_model.objects.emplace_back(*it);
1178 model_object_status_db.add(*mobj, ModelObjectStatus::Moved);
1179 }
1180 }
1181 bool deleted_any = false;
1182 for (ModelObject *&model_object : model_objects_old)
1183 if (model_object_status_db.add_if_new(*model_object, ModelObjectStatus::Deleted))
1184 deleted_any = true;
1185 else
1186 // Do not delete this ModelObject instance.
1187 model_object = nullptr;
1188 if (deleted_any) {
1189 // Delete PrintObjects of the deleted ModelObjects.
1190 PrintObjectPtrs print_objects_old = std::move(m_objects);
1191 m_objects.clear();
1192 m_objects.reserve(print_objects_old.size());
1193 for (PrintObject *print_object : print_objects_old) {
1194 const ModelObjectStatus &status = model_object_status_db.get(*print_object->model_object());
1195 if (status.status == ModelObjectStatus::Deleted) {
1196 update_apply_status(print_object->invalidate_all_steps());
1197 delete print_object;
1198 } else
1199 m_objects.emplace_back(print_object);
1200 }
1201 for (ModelObject *model_object : model_objects_old)
1202 delete model_object;
1203 print_regions_reshuffled = true;
1204 }
1205 }
1206 }

1208 // 2) Map print objects including their transformation matrices.
1209 PrintObjectStatusDB print_object_status_db(m_objects);

1211 // 3) Synchronize ModelObjects & PrintObjects.
1212 const std::initializer_list<ModelVolumeType> solid_or_modifier_types { ModelVolumeType::MODEL_PART, ModelVolumeType::NEGATIVE_VOLUME, ModelVolumeType::PARAMETER_MODIFIER };
1213 for (size_t idx_model_object = 0; idx_model_object < model.objects.size(); ++ idx_model_object) {
1214 ModelObject &model_object = *m_model.objects[idx_model_object];
1215 ModelObjectStatus &model_object_status = const_cast<ModelObjectStatus&>(model_object_status_db.reuse(model_object));
1216 const ModelObject &model_object_new = *model.objects[idx_model_object];
1217 if (model_object_status.status == ModelObjectStatus::New)
1218 // PrintObject instances will be added in the next loop.
1219 continue;
1220 // Update the ModelObject instance, possibly invalidate the linked PrintObjects.
1221 assert(model_object_status.status == ModelObjectStatus::Old || model_object_status.status == ModelObjectStatus::Moved);
1222 // Check whether a model part volume was added or removed, their transformations or order changed.
1223 // Only volume IDs, volume types, transformation matrices and their order are checked, configuration and other parameters are NOT checked.
1224 bool solid_or_modifier_differ = model_volume_list_changed(model_object, model_object_new, solid_or_modifier_types) ||
1225 model_mmu_segmentation_data_changed(model_object, model_object_new) ||
1226 (model_object_new.is_mm_painted() && num_extruders_changed );
1227 bool supports_differ = model_volume_list_changed(model_object, model_object_new, ModelVolumeType::SUPPORT_BLOCKER) ||
1228 model_volume_list_changed(model_object, model_object_new, ModelVolumeType::SUPPORT_ENFORCER);
1229 bool layer_height_ranges_differ = ! layer_height_ranges_equal(model_object.layer_config_ranges, model_object_new.layer_config_ranges, model_object_new.layer_height_profile.empty());
1230 bool model_origin_translation_differ = model_object.origin_translation != model_object_new.origin_translation;
1231 auto print_objects_range = print_object_status_db.get_range(model_object);
1232 // The list actually can be empty if all instances are out of the print bed.
1233 //assert(print_objects_range.begin() != print_objects_range.end());
1234 // All PrintObjects in print_objects_range shall point to the same prints_objects_regions
1235 if (print_objects_range.begin() != print_objects_range.end()) {
1236 model_object_status.print_object_regions = print_objects_range.begin()->print_object->m_shared_regions;
1237 model_object_status.print_object_regions->ref_cnt_inc();
1238 }
1239 if (solid_or_modifier_differ || model_origin_translation_differ || layer_height_ranges_differ ||
1240 ! model_object.layer_height_profile.timestamp_matches(model_object_new.layer_height_profile)) {
1241 // The very first step (the slicing step) is invalidated. One may freely remove all associated PrintObjects.
1242 model_object_status.print_object_regions_status =
1243 model_object_status.print_object_regions == nullptr || model_origin_translation_differ || layer_height_ranges_differ ?
1244 // Drop print_objects_regions.
1245 ModelObjectStatus::PrintObjectRegionsStatus::Invalid :
1246 // Reuse bounding boxes of print_objects_regions for ModelVolumes with unmodified transformation.
1247 ModelObjectStatus::PrintObjectRegionsStatus::PartiallyValid;
1248 for (const PrintObjectStatus &print_object_status : print_objects_range) {
1249 update_apply_status(print_object_status.print_object->invalidate_all_steps());
1250 const_cast<PrintObjectStatus&>(print_object_status).status = PrintObjectStatus::Deleted;
1251 }
1252 if (model_object_status.print_object_regions_status == ModelObjectStatus::PrintObjectRegionsStatus::PartiallyValid)
1253 // Drop everything from PrintObjectRegions but those VolumeExtents (of their particular ModelVolumes) that are still valid.
1254 print_objects_regions_invalidate_keep_some_volumes(*model_object_status.print_object_regions, model_object.volumes, model_object_new.volumes);
1255 else if (model_object_status.print_object_regions != nullptr)
1256 model_object_status.print_object_regions->clear();
1257 // Copy content of the ModelObject including its ID, do not change the parent.
1258 model_object.assign_copy(model_object_new);
1259 } else {
1260 model_object_status.print_object_regions_status = ModelObjectStatus::PrintObjectRegionsStatus::Valid;
1261 if (supports_differ || model_custom_supports_data_changed(model_object, model_object_new)) {
1262 // First stop background processing before shuffling or deleting the ModelVolumes in the ModelObject's list.
1263 if (supports_differ) {
1264 this->call_cancel_callback();
1265 update_apply_status(false);
1266 }
1267 // Invalidate just the supports step.
1268 for (const PrintObjectStatus &print_object_status : print_objects_range)
1269 update_apply_status(print_object_status.print_object->invalidate_step(posSupportMaterial));
1270 if (supports_differ) {
1271 // Copy just the support volumes.
1272 model_volume_list_update_supports(model_object, model_object_new);
1273 }
1274 } else if (model_custom_seam_data_changed(model_object, model_object_new)) {
1275 update_apply_status(this->invalidate_step(psGCodeExport));
1276 }
1277 }
1278 if (! solid_or_modifier_differ) {
1279 // Synchronize Object's config.
1280 bool object_config_changed = ! model_object.config.timestamp_matches(model_object_new.config);
1281 if (object_config_changed)
1282 model_object.config.assign_config(model_object_new.config);
1283 if (! object_diff.empty() || object_config_changed || num_extruders_changed ) {
1284 PrintObjectConfig new_config = PrintObject::object_config_from_model_object(m_default_object_config, model_object, num_extruders );
1285 for (const PrintObjectStatus &print_object_status : print_object_status_db.get_range(model_object)) {
1286 t_config_option_keys diff = print_object_status.print_object->config().diff(new_config);
1287 if (! diff.empty()) {
1288 update_apply_status(print_object_status.print_object->invalidate_state_by_config_options(print_object_status.print_object->config(), new_config, diff));
1289 print_object_status.print_object->config_apply_only(new_config, diff, true);
1290 }
1291 }
1292 }
1293 // Synchronize (just copy) the remaining data of ModelVolumes (name, config, custom supports data).
1294 //FIXME What to do with m_material_id?
1295 model_volume_list_copy_configs(model_object /* dst */, model_object_new /* src */, ModelVolumeType::MODEL_PART);
1296 model_volume_list_copy_configs(model_object /* dst */, model_object_new /* src */, ModelVolumeType::PARAMETER_MODIFIER);
1297 layer_height_ranges_copy_configs(model_object.layer_config_ranges /* dst */, model_object_new.layer_config_ranges /* src */);
1298 // Copy the ModelObject name, input_file and instances. The instances will be compared against PrintObject instances in the next step.
1299 model_object.name = model_object_new.name;
1300 model_object.input_file = model_object_new.input_file;
1301 // Only refresh ModelInstances if there is any change.
1302 if (model_object.instances.size() != model_object_new.instances.size() ||
1303 ! std::equal(model_object.instances.begin(), model_object.instances.end(), model_object_new.instances.begin(), [](auto l, auto r){ return l->id() == r->id(); })) {
1304 // G-code generator accesses model_object.instances to generate sequential print ordering matching the Plater object list.
1305 update_apply_status(this->invalidate_step(psGCodeExport));
1306 model_object.clear_instances();
1307 model_object.instances.reserve(model_object_new.instances.size());
1308 for (const ModelInstance *model_instance : model_object_new.instances) {
1309 model_object.instances.emplace_back(new ModelInstance(*model_instance));
1310 model_object.instances.back()->set_model_object(&model_object);
1311 }
1312 } else if (! std::equal(model_object.instances.begin(), model_object.instances.end(), model_object_new.instances.begin(),
1313 [](auto l, auto r){ return l->print_volume_state == r->print_volume_state && l->printable == r->printable &&
1314 l->get_transformation().get_matrix().isApprox(r->get_transformation().get_matrix()); })) {
1315 // If some of the instances changed, the bounding box of the updated ModelObject is likely no more valid.
1316 // This is safe as the ModelObject's bounding box is only accessed from this function, which is called from the main thread only.
1317 model_object.invalidate_bounding_box();
1318 // Synchronize the content of instances.
1319 auto new_instance = model_object_new.instances.begin();
1320 for (auto old_instance = model_object.instances.begin(); old_instance != model_object.instances.end(); ++ old_instance, ++ new_instance) {
1321 (*old_instance)->set_transformation((*new_instance)->get_transformation());
1322 (*old_instance)->print_volume_state = (*new_instance)->print_volume_state;
1323 (*old_instance)->printable = (*new_instance)->printable;
1324 }
1325 }

1329 // 4) Generate PrintObjects from ModelObjects and their instances.
1330 {
1331 PrintObjectPtrs print_objects_new;
1332 print_objects_new.reserve(std::max(m_objects.size(), m_model.objects.size()));
1333 bool new_objects = false;
1334 // Walk over all new model objects and check, whether there are matching PrintObjects.
1335 for (ModelObject *model_object : m_model.objects) {
1336 ModelObjectStatus &model_object_status = const_cast<ModelObjectStatus&>(model_object_status_db.reuse(*model_object));
1337 model_object_status.print_instances = print_objects_from_model_object(*model_object);
1338 std::vector<const PrintObjectStatus*> old;
1339 old.reserve(print_object_status_db.count(*model_object));
1340 for (const PrintObjectStatus &print_object_status : print_object_status_db.get_range(*model_object))
1341 if (print_object_status.status != PrintObjectStatus::Deleted)
1342 old.emplace_back(&print_object_status);
1343 // Generate a list of trafos and XY offsets for instances of a ModelObject
1344 // Producing the config for PrintObject on demand, caching it at print_object_last.
1345 const PrintObject *print_object_last = nullptr;
1346 auto print_object_apply_config = [this, &print_object_last, model_object, num_extruders ](PrintObject *print_object) {
1347 print_object->config_apply(print_object_last ?
1348 print_object_last->config() :
1349 PrintObject::object_config_from_model_object(m_default_object_config, *model_object, num_extruders ));
1350 print_object_last = print_object;
1351 };
1352 if (old.empty()) {
1353 // Simple case, just generate new instances.
1354 for (PrintObjectTrafoAndInstances &print_instances : model_object_status.print_instances) {
1355 PrintObject *print_object = new PrintObject(this, model_object, print_instances.trafo, std::move(print_instances.instances));
1356 print_object_apply_config(print_object);
1357 print_objects_new.emplace_back(print_object);
1358 // print_object_status.emplace(PrintObjectStatus(print_object, PrintObjectStatus::New));
1359 new_objects = true;
1360 }
1361 continue;
1362 }
1363 // Complex case, try to merge the two lists.
1364 // Sort the old lexicographically by their trafos.
1365 std::sort(old.begin(), old.end(), [](const PrintObjectStatus *lhs, const PrintObjectStatus *rhs){ return transform3d_lower(lhs->trafo, rhs->trafo); });
1366 // Merge the old / new lists.
1367 auto it_old = old.begin();
1368 for (PrintObjectTrafoAndInstances &new_instances : model_object_status.print_instances) {
1369 for (; it_old != old.end() && transform3d_lower((*it_old)->trafo, new_instances.trafo); ++ it_old);
1370 if (it_old == old.end() || ! transform3d_equal((*it_old)->trafo, new_instances.trafo)) {
1371 // This is a new instance (or a set of instances with the same trafo). Just add it.
1372 PrintObject *print_object = new PrintObject(this, model_object, new_instances.trafo, std::move(new_instances.instances));
1373 print_object_apply_config(print_object);
1374 print_objects_new.emplace_back(print_object);
1375 // print_object_status.emplace(PrintObjectStatus(print_object, PrintObjectStatus::New));
1376 new_objects = true;
1377 if (it_old != old.end())
1378 const_cast<PrintObjectStatus*>(*it_old)->status = PrintObjectStatus::Deleted;
1379 } else {
1380 // The PrintObject already exists and the copies differ.
1381 PrintBase::ApplyStatus status = (*it_old)->print_object->set_instances(std::move(new_instances.instances));
1382 if (status != PrintBase::APPLY_STATUS_UNCHANGED)
1383 update_apply_status(status == PrintBase::APPLY_STATUS_INVALIDATED);
1384 print_objects_new.emplace_back((*it_old)->print_object);
1385 const_cast<PrintObjectStatus*>(*it_old)->status = PrintObjectStatus::Reused;
1386 }
1387 }
1388 }
1389 if (m_objects != print_objects_new) {
1390 //BBS: add more logs
1391 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(" %1%: found print object changed.")%__LINE__;
1392 this->call_cancel_callback();
1393 update_apply_status(this->invalidate_all_steps());
1394 m_objects = print_objects_new;
1395 // Delete the PrintObjects marked as Unknown or Deleted.
1396 bool deleted_objects = false;
1397 for (const PrintObjectStatus &pos : print_object_status_db)
1398 if (pos.status == PrintObjectStatus::Unknown || pos.status == PrintObjectStatus::Deleted) {
1399 update_apply_status(pos.print_object->invalidate_all_steps());
1400 delete pos.print_object;
1401 deleted_objects = true;
1402 }
1403 if (new_objects || deleted_objects)
1404 update_apply_status(this->invalidate_steps({ psSkirtBrim, psWipeTower, psGCodeExport }));
1405 if (new_objects)
1406 update_apply_status(false);
1407 print_regions_reshuffled = true;
1408 }
1409 print_object_status_db.clear();

1412 for (PrintObject* object : m_objects) {
1413 auto ept_iter = std::find(print_diff.begin(), print_diff.end(), "enable_prime_tower");
1414 if (/*object->config().adaptive_layer_height &&*/ ept_iter != print_diff.end()) {
1415 update_apply_status(object->invalidate_step(posSlice));
1416 }
1417 }
1418 }

1420 //BBS: check the config again
1421 int new_used_filaments = this->extruders(true).size();
1422 t_config_option_keys new_changed_keys = new_full_config.normalize_fdm_2(objects().size(), new_used_filaments);
1423 if (new_changed_keys.size() > 0) {
1424 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(", got new_changed_keys, size=%1%")%new_changed_keys.size();
1425 for (int i = 0; i < new_changed_keys.size(); i++)
1426 {
1427 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(", i=%1%, key=%2%")%i %new_changed_keys[i];
1428 }

1430 update_apply_status(false);
1431
1432 // The following call may stop the background processing.
1433 update_apply_status(this->invalidate_state_by_config_options(new_full_config, new_changed_keys));
1434
1435 update_apply_status(this->invalidate_step(psGCodeExport));

1437 if (full_config_diff.empty()) {
1438 //BBS: previous empty
1439 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(" %1%: full_config_diff previous empty, need to apply now.")%__LINE__;

1441 m_placeholder_parser.clear_config();
1442 // Set the profile aliases for the PrintBase::output_filename()
1443 m_placeholder_parser.set("print_preset", new_full_config.option("print_settings_id")->clone());
1444 m_placeholder_parser.set("filament_preset", new_full_config.option("filament_settings_id")->clone());
1445 m_placeholder_parser.set("printer_preset", new_full_config.option("printer_settings_id")->clone());
1446
1447 //m_placeholder_parser.apply_config(filament_overrides);
1448 }
1449 // It is also safe to change m_config now after this->invalidate_state_by_config_options() call.
1450 m_config.apply_only(new_full_config, new_changed_keys, true);
1451 // Handle changes to object config defaults
1452 m_default_object_config.apply_only(new_full_config, new_changed_keys, true);
1453 // Handle changes to regions config defaults
1454 m_default_region_config.apply_only(new_full_config, new_changed_keys, true);
1455 m_full_print_config = std::move(new_full_config);

1458 // All regions now have distinct settings.
1459 // Check whether applying the new region config defaults we would get different regions,
1460 // update regions or create regions from scratch.
1461 for (auto it_print_object = m_objects.begin(); it_print_object != m_objects.end();) {
1462 // Find the range of PrintObjects sharing the same associated ModelObject.
1463 auto it_print_object_end = it_print_object;
1464 PrintObject &print_object = *(*it_print_object);
1465 const ModelObject &model_object = *print_object.model_object();
1466 ModelObjectStatus &model_object_status = const_cast<ModelObjectStatus&>(model_object_status_db.reuse(model_object));
1467 PrintObjectRegions *print_object_regions = model_object_status.print_object_regions;
1468 for (++ it_print_object_end; it_print_object_end != m_objects.end() && (*it_print_object)->model_object() == (*it_print_object_end)->model_object(); ++ it_print_object_end)
1469 assert((*it_print_object_end)->m_shared_regions == nullptr || (*it_print_object_end)->m_shared_regions == print_object_regions);
1470 if (print_object_regions == nullptr) {
1471 print_object_regions = new PrintObjectRegions{};
1472 model_object_status.print_object_regions = print_object_regions;
1473 print_object_regions->ref_cnt_inc();
1474 }
1475 std::vector<unsigned int> painting_extruders;
1476 if (const auto &volumes = print_object.model_object()->volumes;
1477 num_extruders > 1 &&
1478 std::find_if(volumes.begin(), volumes.end(), [](const ModelVolume *v) { return ! v->mmu_segmentation_facets.empty(); }) != volumes.end()) {
1479 //FIXME be more specific! Don't enumerate extruders that are not used for painting!
1480 painting_extruders.assign(num_extruders , 0);
1481 std::iota(painting_extruders.begin(), painting_extruders.end(), 1);

1483 if (model_object_status.print_object_regions_status == ModelObjectStatus::PrintObjectRegionsStatus::Valid) {
1484 // Verify that the trafo for regions & volume bounding boxes thus for regions is still applicable.
1485 auto invalidate = [it_print_object, it_print_object_end, update_apply_status]() {
1486 for (auto it = it_print_object; it != it_print_object_end; ++ it)
1487 if ((*it)->m_shared_regions != nullptr)
1488 update_apply_status((*it)->invalidate_all_steps());

1490 if (print_object_regions && ! trafos_differ_in_rotation_by_z_and_mirroring_by_xy_only(print_object_regions->trafo_bboxes, model_object_status.print_instances.front().trafo)) {
1491 invalidate();
1492 print_object_regions->clear();
1493 model_object_status.print_object_regions_status = ModelObjectStatus::PrintObjectRegionsStatus::Invalid;
1494 print_regions_reshuffled = true;
1495 } else if (print_object_regions &&
1496 verify_update_print_object_regions(
1497 print_object.model_object()->volumes,
1498 m_default_region_config,
1499 num_extruders ,
1500 painting_extruders,
1501 *print_object_regions,
1502 [it_print_object, it_print_object_end, &update_apply_status](const PrintRegionConfig &old_config, const PrintRegionConfig &new_config, const t_config_option_keys &diff_keys) {
1503 for (auto it = it_print_object; it != it_print_object_end; ++it)
1504 if ((*it)->m_shared_regions != nullptr)
1505 update_apply_status((*it)->invalidate_state_by_config_options(old_config, new_config, diff_keys));
1506 })) {
1507 // Regions are valid, just keep them.
1508 } else {
1509 // Regions were reshuffled.
1510 invalidate();
1511 // At least reuse layer ranges and bounding boxes of ModelVolumes.
1512 model_object_status.print_object_regions_status = ModelObjectStatus::PrintObjectRegionsStatus::PartiallyValid;
1513 print_regions_reshuffled = true;
1514 }
1515 }
1516 if (print_object_regions == nullptr || model_object_status.print_object_regions_status != ModelObjectStatus::PrintObjectRegionsStatus::Valid) {
1517 // Layer ranges with their associated configurations. Remove overlaps between the ranges
1518 // and create the regions from scratch.
1519 print_object_regions = generate_print_object_regions(
1520 print_object_regions,
1521 print_object.model_object()->volumes,
1522 LayerRanges(print_object.model_object()->layer_config_ranges),
1523 m_default_region_config,
1524 model_object_status.print_instances.front().trafo,
1525 num_extruders ,
1526 print_object.is_mm_painted() ? 0.f : float(print_object.config().xy_contour_compensation.value),
1527 painting_extruders);
1528 }
1529 for (auto it = it_print_object; it != it_print_object_end; ++it)
1530 if ((*it)->m_shared_regions) {
1531 assert((*it)->m_shared_regions == print_object_regions);
1532 } else {
1533 (*it)->m_shared_regions = print_object_regions;
1534 print_object_regions->ref_cnt_inc();
1535 }
1536 it_print_object = it_print_object_end;
1537 }

1539 if (print_regions_reshuffled) {
1540 // Update Print::m_print_regions from objects.
1541 struct cmp { bool operator() (const PrintRegion *l, const PrintRegion *r) const { return l->config_hash() == r->config_hash() && l->config() == r->config(); } };
1542 std::set<const PrintRegion*, cmp> region_set;
1543 m_print_regions.clear();
1544 PrintObjectRegions *print_object_regions = nullptr;
1545 for (PrintObject *print_object : m_objects)
1546 if (print_object_regions != print_object->m_shared_regions) {
1547 print_object_regions = print_object->m_shared_regions;
1548 for (std::unique_ptr<Slic3r::PrintRegion> &print_region : print_object_regions->all_regions)
1549 if (auto it = region_set.find(print_region.get()); it == region_set.end()) {
1550 int print_region_id = int(m_print_regions.size());
1551 m_print_regions.emplace_back(print_region.get());
1552 print_region->m_print_region_id = print_region_id;
1553 } else {
1554 print_region->m_print_region_id = (*it)->print_region_id();
1555 }
1556 }
1557 }

1559 // Update SlicingParameters for each object where the SlicingParameters is not valid.
1560 // If it is not valid, then it is ensured that PrintObject.m_slicing_params is not in use
1561 // (posSlicing and posSupportMaterial was invalidated).
1562 for (PrintObject *object : m_objects)
1563 {
1564 object->update_slicing_parameters();
1565 m_support_used |= object->config().enable_support;
1566 }

1568#ifdef _DEBUG
1569 check_model_ids_equal(m_model, model);
1570#endif /* _DEBUG */
1571
1572 //BBS: add timestamp logic
